1) NEVER use Bolt Database or Supabase.
2) Use React for frontend and Node.js for backend.
3) Backend must always use PostgreSQL as the database.
4) Create all README files only inside the /READMEs folder.
5) Frontend UI must always be modern, compact, and fully responsive on desktop/tablet/mobile.
6) All backend API URLs must be read from VITE_API_BASE_URL environment variable.
7) Follow this folder structure: frontend/ (components, pages, services, layouts), backend/ (routes, controllers, services, models, middlewares), READMEs/, scripts/, migrations/, config.
8) Frontend must follow a component-based structure: /components, /pages, /layouts, /hooks, /context, /services, /utils.
9) All API calls from the frontend must be done through a single centralized HTTP wrapper inside /services/http.service.js.
10) Each API entity (Spaces, News, Auth, Users, etc.) must have its own API module inside /services/ (e.g., spaces.api.js, news.api.js)
11) Frontend must support runtime environment variables using public/env.js and read values using window.__ENV.*.
12) Backend must follow clean layering: /routes → /controllers → /services → /models → /config.
13) All backend routes must follow REST standards and begin with /api/....
14) Backend must store database config, environment loader, and logger inside /config.
15) SQL queries or Prisma models must be organized inside /models.
16) Backend must contain /middlewares for authentication, validation, and error handling.
17) Project folder structure must follow: frontend/, backend/, READMEs/, scripts/, migrations/, config/.
18) UI must strictly follow the FUSO brand theme using black (#000000), red (#E60000), and light grey (#f5f5f7).
19) Black (#000000) should not exceed 30% of any page (used mainly for headings, text, icons, and key sections).
20) Red (#E60000) should be used as the primary accent color and must not exceed 10% per page (used for CTAs, highlights, and action elements).
21) Light grey (#f5f5f7) must cover at least 60% of every page (as the main background and layout base).
22)All primary action buttons must use the brand secondary color red (#E60000).
23) Cancel buttons or non-primary actions must use neutral colors (black outline or grey tones).